criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. Diagnosis is ST-elevated acute myocardial infarction based by WHO standard;
2. Less than 1 month since the onset of ST-AMI;
3. Successfully vessel reconstructed and TIMI>3;
4. Age>18 years old;
5. Patients who sign informed consent form and can finish whole follow-up.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. Patients who are complicated with other heart disease, including:
Refractory sustained ventricle tachycardia;
Severe heart block and not controlled by heart pace maker;
Genetic heart disease;
Primary heart valve disease;
Active myocarditis;
Pulmonary heart disease, etc.;
2. Liver or kidney dysfunction (ALT>80U/L, Cr>440mmol/L);
3. Patients with autoimmune disease or any other severe fatality disease;
4. Patients have contradictions of percutaneous coronary intervention;
5. Patients with psychiatric disease.
